            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>随著市场对轻松骑行的需求不断增长，电动辅助自行车的普及度也逐渐上升。不过，电动自行车需要依赖充电，且电池与马达的使用寿命有限。为了应对这些问题，日本汽车部件制造商推出了一项不需要电力驱动、仅依靠弹簧原理来减轻骑行负担的新技术。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda041screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304285" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda041screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda041screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda041screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda010screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304273" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda010screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda010screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda010screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda013screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304274" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda013screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda013screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda013screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>这项名为「Reloda」的技术，其灵感来自汽车离合器中的阻尼器。其基本运作方式是，当骑行者踩下脚踏板时，大盘中的弹簧会被压缩，然后弹簧反弹的力量会推动脚踏板，从而减轻脚部的施力。根据日本神户大学的研究，这项技术能有效减少约 20% 的肌肉负担，让骑行者能够轻松完成长时间骑行。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113389-1.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304282" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113389-1-694x455.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="455" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113389-1-694x455.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113389-1.jpg 915w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113390.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304281" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113390.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="426" /></a></p><p>该技术的运作过程也极为简单，当脚踏板被踩下时，弹簧会进行压缩，并储存能量。随著脚踏板的回弹，弹簧会释放这些储存的能量，并有效推动脚踏板前进。这样的设计使得骑行者在踩踏过程中所需的力量大大减少，从而减轻了肌肉的疲劳。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda155screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304275" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda155screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda155screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda155screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>「Reloda」技术的核心是模拟汽车离合器中的减震器，这一创新不仅解决了电动辅助自行车的充电问题，还能帮助使用者提高骑行效率，无论是长时间的平地骑行还是爬坡，都能减少肌肉负担。这项技术的研发不仅代表著汽车零部件技术在自行车领域的应用，也显示出弹簧技术在未来可能的广泛应用。</p><p>在神户大学的研究中，实验显示，使用这项技术的自行车相比传统车型能显著减少人体的肌肉负担。研究表明，当骑行者佩戴 Reloda 系统时，脚部所需施加的力量减少了 20%，这一数据对于长途骑行者来说，无疑是一大福音。这项技术的出现不仅让骑行变得更轻松，还能提高整体骑行体验，进一步吸引了那些长时间骑行的消费者。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113393-1.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304284" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113393-1-647x580.jpg" alt="" width="647" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113393-1-647x580.jpg 647w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/113393-1.jpg 960w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 647px" /></a></p><p>以下是每个旋转角度的详细解释，说明 Reloda 技术在每个阶段如何减轻骑行者的肌肉负担：</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda118screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304264" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda118screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda118screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda118screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲0 度：当脚踏板在起始位置，即刚开始踩踏时，弹簧开始受到压缩。此时，弹簧储存能量，准备在接下来的过程中释放，帮助脚踏板向下移动。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda122screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304265" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda122screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda122screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda122screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲45 度：当骑行者的脚开始踩下踏板时，弹簧继续压缩。这时候，弹簧的力量开始提供支持，减少了脚部需要施加的力量。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda126screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304266" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda126screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda126screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda126screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲90 度：在这个角度，弹簧处于接近最大压缩状态，为骑行者提供最大的支持，并减少了肌肉负担，特别是对于下压踏板的时候。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda130screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304267" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda130screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda130screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda130screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲135 度：此时，弹簧开始释放储存的能量，并继续向外伸展，帮助脚踏板向前进行转动。骑行者的肌肉负担再次减少，并进一步支持下个踏板移动。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda135screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304268" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda135screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda135screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda135screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲180 度：当脚踏板达到半圈的位置时，弹簧基本上已经完成了最大的压缩并开始向外反弹，进一步帮助推动踏板，使脚步更轻松。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda139screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304269" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda139screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda139screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda139screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲225 度：当踏板接近后半圈时，弹簧继续伸展并提供反向支持，减少骑行者在这一阶段所需的肌肉力量，帮助完成踏板的转动。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda143screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304270" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda143screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda143screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda143screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲270 度：这时弹簧接近完全伸展，对骑行者的支持达到最大，帮助骑行者维持稳定的力量输出，减少肌肉的过度使用。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda148screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304271" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda148screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda148screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda148screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲315 度：踏板接近一圈的结束，弹簧的反弹动作继续协助脚踏板进行旋转，这有助于进入下一个踏板循环，减少每次踩踏所需的力量。</p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda153screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304272" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda153screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda153screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda153screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a><br />
▲360 度：当踏板完成一圈后，弹簧的能量基本上已经完全释放并准备重新压缩。此时，骑行者的肌肉负担减少，并准备开始新的踏板循环。</p><p>总结来说，Reloda 技术通过弹簧在不同角度的压缩和反弹来辅助骑行者，在踩踏过程中逐步提供支援，减少肌肉的使用，从而提高骑行效率，特别是在长时间和高强度的骑行中能够显著减轻疲劳。</p><p>目前，这项技术的专利已经申请成功，并且正在向市场推广。虽然目前的测试结果显示它在减轻肌肉负担方面已经取得了不小的成效，但未来仍有进一步改良的空间，特别是在如何进一步优化弹簧设计和提高其耐用性方面。</p><p><a href="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda231screenshot.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1304276" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda231screenshot-694x390.jpeg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda231screenshot-694x390.jpeg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/reloda231screenshot.jpeg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></a></p><p>随著这项技术的应用，未来我们或许能见到更多无需电池和充电的轻松骑行体验，这无疑将对自行车市场产生深远影响。至于未来，Reloda 技术是否能成为新一代骑行装置的标配，还需要时间来验证。</p><div class="epyt-video-wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy"  style="display: block; margin: 0px auto;"  id="_ytid_63274"  width="590" height="332"  data-origwidth="590" data-origheight="332" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/PalU7iluEFE?enablejsapi=1&#038;autoplay=0&#038;cc_load_policy=0&#038;cc_lang_pref=&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;loop=0&#038;modestbranding=1&#038;rel=0&#038;fs=1&#038;playsinline=1&#038;autohide=1&#038;theme=light&#038;color=white&#038;controls=1&#038;" class="__youtube_prefs__  epyt-is-override  no-lazyload" title="YouTube player"  allow="fullscreen; accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen data-no-lazy="1" data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll=""></iframe></div><p>资料来源：<a href="https://carcareplus.jp/article/2025/04/20/11346.html">Carcareplus</a></p><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2025/04/20/reloda/life-tech/bike/">毋须用电，只用弹簧减轻骑单车负担，日本新技术 Reloda 省力最高达 20%</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
